          "SERVICE_USER"
        ]
      },
      "date": "2012-10-08 14:56:08.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: Verified\n\nTests received by maloo, run on CentOS release 6.3/x86_64, CentOS release 5.8/x86_64: (https://maloo.whamcloud.com/test_sessions/9a6b48ae-1154-11e2-a645-52540035b04c).  Ran 12 tests.  No failures.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "e86410aa40dbd9e9faa8432ce5e62d1ce74b4ed7",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2012-10-08 15:06:28.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: Looks good to me, but someone else must approve\n\nIf we are going to keep the debugging, then dr_line could be __u16 and follow dr_flags to avoid making the struct larger. \n\nAlso, is there a risk that this function will skip seeing the \"1\" value due to race condition between reading the atomic and other threads decrementing it?  It would be possible to set the dr_completed by every thread, and the the last one will be the most uptodate.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "549ada2aaf61562c36dae3d307980ba8e04c9019",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 119,
        "name": "Alex Zhuravlev",
        "email": "bzzz@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "bzzz"
      },
      "date": "2012-10-08 15:20:40.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n> If we are going to keep the debugging, then dr_line could be __u16 and follow dr_flags to avoid making the struct larger.\n\nI'd rather drop this once the issue is solved.\n\n> Also, is there a risk that this function will skip seeing the \"1\" value due to race condition between reading the atomic and other threads decrementing it? It would be possible to set the dr_completed by every thread, and the the last one will be the most uptodate.\n\nit's decremented only in this place (bio completion routine). though it's possible we get to 0 few times as few bios can be issued to handle a set of blocks. but this should be fine as we literally set dr_elapsed to a new value.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "5f29ec189a8c1f490ea32fc175f42ca0336ffd2a",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 112,
        "name": "Oleg Drokin",
        "email": "green@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "green"
      },
      "date": "2012-10-09 21:40:33.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: Looks good to me, approved\n\nIn the end I believe this patch greatly improves situation in my testing, so no reason to not land it.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
